
[1]sickness

   SICK'NESS, n.

   1. Nausea; squeamishness; as sickness of the stomach.

   2. State of being diseased. I do lament the sickness of the king.

   3. Disease; malady; a morbid state of the body of an animal or plant,
   in which the organs do not perfectly perform their natural functions.
   Trust not too much your now resistless charms; Those age or sickness
   soon or late disarms. Himself took our infirmities, and bore our
   sicknesses. Matt 8.
